486
00:25:09,847 --> 00:25:11,953
Oshi's on his way up!

487
00:25:12,517 --> 00:25:14,183
He's here.

488
00:25:18,075 --> 00:25:22,861
The master of minimal,
the king of clean...

489
00:25:23,015 --> 00:25:26,383
Marc... the champagne.

490
00:25:29,466 --> 00:25:31,723
Ohayo gozaimasu, Oshi-san.

491
00:25:33,218 --> 00:25:37,821
Good morning.
I'm very thirsty. Are you?

492
00:25:42,447 --> 00:25:44,461
We have fresh coffee.

493
00:25:47,097 --> 00:25:50,772
I am very thirsty for some champagne,
Oshi, are you?

494
00:25:50,787 --> 00:25:52,202
Wilhelmina.

495
00:25:55,196 --> 00:25:56,921
- Champagne.
- Kampai, darling.

496
00:25:56,937 --> 00:25:58,693
- Kampai.
- Kampai.

497
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,573
Daniel Meade...

498
00:26:03,585 --> 00:26:06,502
I will be fitting my spring
collection on my Models

499
00:26:06,515 --> 00:26:08,441
today and tomorrow.

500
00:26:08,675 --> 00:26:11,182
Tomorrow evening I will
return to do a showing

501
00:26:11,197 --> 00:26:13,132
for you and your editors.

502
00:26:13,975 --> 00:26:17,742
We will use your tube
entry for our runway walk.

503
00:26:18,475 --> 00:26:20,361
I like it...

504
00:26:20,376 --> 00:26:24,113
round, white, minimal.

505
00:26:25,825 --> 00:26:27,823
Then we will drink champagne,

506
00:26:27,837 --> 00:26:31,152
and you will take us out
for a wonderful meal.

507
00:26:31,566 --> 00:26:35,110
After that,
we will talk business...

508
00:26:35,305 --> 00:26:36,962
or not.

509
00:26:43,377 --> 00:26:47,371
He said "a wonderful meal." He's
expecting a wonderful meal.

510
00:26:48,148 --> 00:26:51,180
Well, I'd be happy to
pick up the tab, Daniel.

511
00:26:51,197 --> 00:26:52,683
I can treat.

512
00:26:52,697 --> 00:26:56,910
Of course, then you'd have
to invite me to the dinner.

513
00:27:00,427 --> 00:27:01,970
She knows I'm broke.

514
00:27:01,987 --> 00:27:04,901
She knew before she
met with my father.

515
00:27:04,917 --> 00:27:08,412
Daniel, I don't think it's really a good
idea to let Wilhelmina pay for dinner.

516
00:27:08,427 --> 00:27:11,260
I mean, the japanese are very attuned
to nuance, and it would appear

517
00:27:11,277 --> 00:27:12,473
that you're not in charge.

518
00:27:12,488 --> 00:27:14,832
Oh, right, I-I get it, okay?

519
00:27:14,848 --> 00:27:17,041
But I don't have
a choice, right?

520
00:27:17,056 --> 00:27:19,380
I mean,
if I use Wilhelmina's expense account,

521
00:27:19,396 --> 00:27:22,202
she gets credit for keeping Oshi,
and my father knows I'm broke,

522
00:27:22,216 --> 00:27:24,872
but if I don't use her,
we risk losing Oshi,

523
00:27:24,887 --> 00:27:26,923
and he really knows I'm broke.

524
00:27:26,935 --> 00:27:29,470
Either way, I end up looking
like a financial incompetent,

525
00:27:29,487 --> 00:27:31,072
and she gets the
publisher's job.

526
00:27:31,085 --> 00:27:34,220
Well, not if you can
impress Oshi under $300,

527
00:27:34,237 --> 00:27:36,183
and there are some really
great things on this list.

528
00:27:36,218 --> 00:27:38,793
$300 won't buy Oshi
a new scrunchie.

529
00:27:38,805 --> 00:27:41,051
We could take him
to the movies...

530
00:27:41,067 --> 00:27:44,460
or, um, okay, uh,
the Statue of Liberty...

531
00:27:44,475 --> 00:27:46,812
or you know what?
Walter and I had so much fun

532
00:27:46,828 --> 00:27:50,933
eating at Papaya Queen and riding
the Staten Island ferry, really.

533
00:27:51,248 --> 00:27:54,040
The ferry, Betty? Really?

534
00:27:54,125 --> 00:27:55,320
Yeah.

535
00:27:57,065 --> 00:27:59,770
Yeah. Oh, let's forget it.

536
00:27:59,788 --> 00:28:02,450
Wilhelmina got us.
This is over.

537
00:28:02,515 --> 00:28:04,033
We're done.

538
00:28:04,707 --> 00:28:07,513
Well, it's his own fault
for spending so much.

539
00:28:07,527 --> 00:28:09,882
Yeah, but I filled out
his expense report.

540
00:28:09,895 --> 00:28:12,011
No, no, no, no, no,
you just didn't lie for him.

541
00:28:12,026 --> 00:28:14,202
Listen, they're all at it.
They all cheat.

542
00:28:14,215 --> 00:28:16,952
Wilhelmina, especially.
They abuse their expense accounts

543
00:28:16,967 --> 00:28:19,722
like it's their god-given right,
and they pay us slave wages.

544
00:28:19,738 --> 00:28:22,681
- Nice Gucci.
- Thank you.

545
00:28:23,747 --> 00:28:26,340
Oh, it's the last salad.

546
00:28:26,358 --> 00:28:27,872
That's okay.

547
00:28:28,928 --> 00:28:31,093
We carb-loading for a marathon?

548
00:28:31,107 --> 00:28:33,293
We can't all live on laxatives.

549
00:28:36,496 --> 00:28:38,063
Hey, Betty.

550
00:28:38,075 --> 00:28:39,463
Seamstress.

551
00:28:39,476 --> 00:28:42,093
See, the girl from styles
who got my Louboutin boots--

552
00:28:42,105 --> 00:28:43,693
she would die to
have your Gucci bag.

553
00:28:43,708 --> 00:28:46,752
So here's the deal--I will trade
you my season tickets to the opera

554
00:28:46,766 --> 00:28:49,402
for your bag.
Then I can trade your bag for my boots,

555
00:28:49,416 --> 00:28:51,020
and everyone winds up a winner.

556
00:28:51,035 --> 00:28:53,191
The opera? She lives in Queens.

557
00:28:53,205 --> 00:28:56,913
If she wants to hear fat italians
screaming, she can open her window.

558
00:28:56,928 --> 00:28:58,593
Betty loves her new bag.
Don't you?

559
00:28:58,605 --> 00:29:00,621
- Yes, I do.
- There you go, then.

560
00:29:00,638 --> 00:29:02,843
Go away and throw up your
celery sticks. Shoo!

561
00:29:03,605 --> 00:29:05,112
Opera tickets?

562
00:29:05,125 --> 00:29:08,351
Christina, how much
exactly is this bag worth?

563
00:29:08,367 --> 00:29:11,001
Retail? About $4,500.

564
00:29:11,018 --> 00:29:14,622
With the pickle,
however, $4,200.

565
00:29:29,795 --> 00:29:32,160
Please just go home, Walter.

566
00:29:32,355 --> 00:29:33,940
Leave me alone.

567
00:29:56,165 --> 00:29:57,292
I'm home.

568
00:29:57,308 --> 00:30:00,303
We didn't want to start without you,
but it was getting cold.

569
00:30:00,726 --> 00:30:02,331
I went to see Maria.

570
00:30:02,437 --> 00:30:04,363
She gave you 15 refills.

571
00:30:04,377 --> 00:30:07,943
15? You wanna tell me how you
got her to give you 15 refills?

572
00:30:07,957 --> 00:30:09,471
Where's your Gucci?

573
00:30:16,046 --> 00:30:17,922
- Betty...
- It's okay.

574
00:30:17,935 --> 00:30:20,083
It was swag, part of my wages.

575
00:30:20,098 --> 00:30:23,832
That witch blows 25 grand in Rio,
and you've gotta give up your purse--

576
00:30:23,845 --> 00:30:26,383
- Hilda, it's okay.
- No, it's not okay, Betty.

577
00:30:26,398 --> 00:30:27,933
Well, that's the way it is.

578
00:30:32,566 --> 00:30:33,723
I got it.

579
00:30:42,545 --> 00:30:43,592
Hey.

580
00:30:46,357 --> 00:30:50,032
Do you remember how angry you were
when mom gave me her good purse?

581
00:30:50,508 --> 00:30:53,262
Yeah, well... you were 3,

582
00:30:53,887 --> 00:30:57,272
and you used it to carry
around your crayons.

583
00:30:57,988 --> 00:31:01,372
I finally figured out why she
gave it to me and not to you.

584
00:31:01,387 --> 00:31:03,001
Díga me.

585
00:31:03,817 --> 00:31:06,430
She knew how it
would make me feel.

586
00:31:10,467 --> 00:31:13,941
Christina says that fashion
is good for the soul...

587
00:31:15,357 --> 00:31:18,603
and when I was walking
around with my Gucci today,

588
00:31:19,686 --> 00:31:23,743
it was like I was 3 years old
again and holding mom's purse...

589
00:31:26,317 --> 00:31:28,413
and I actually felt pretty.

590
00:31:31,326 --> 00:31:32,990
I know, mama.

591
00:31:43,426 --> 00:31:47,290
Well, you had to do it, Betty.
No matter how much you loved the bag,

592
00:31:47,306 --> 00:31:49,710
- you did the right thing.
- I know.

593
00:31:49,726 --> 00:31:52,283
So then you went and got
a bag from the corner guy?

594
00:31:52,297 --> 00:31:55,353
Are you kidding me?
No, that thing costs, like, $200.

595
00:31:55,367 --> 00:31:58,110
I just kept thinking about what
Hilda said, about how unfair it was

596
00:31:58,126 --> 00:32:01,652
that Wilhelmina goes to Rio to
spend $25,000 on props and extras.

597
00:32:01,666 --> 00:32:03,530
We couldn't even afford
medicine for my dad.

598
00:32:03,547 --> 00:32:08,471
Totally, and you have no idea
how they pad their expenses.

599
00:32:11,947 --> 00:32:13,833
Don't stop on my account.

600
00:32:14,227 --> 00:32:16,183
Well, that's exactly
what I was thinking.

601
00:32:16,196 --> 00:32:19,913
So I told Justin to bring me his
issue with the Rio spread, and he did.

602
00:32:21,208 --> 00:32:23,150
Hello. Where's the Gucci?

603
00:32:23,165 --> 00:32:25,400
I didn't want to get
another pickle on it.

604
00:32:25,655 --> 00:32:28,852
Okay, so I realize the opera
tickets were totally inappropriate.

605
00:32:28,868 --> 00:32:32,480
Here is a menudo box set and
a coupon for 100 taquitos.

606
00:32:33,065 --> 00:32:34,373
What?

607
00:32:38,916 --> 00:32:41,021
- I don't have much time.
- That makes two of us.

608
00:32:41,035 --> 00:32:43,600
I need to see Wilhelmina's expense
report from the last issue--

609
00:32:43,615 --> 00:32:44,530
the real one.

610
00:32:44,545 --> 00:32:45,971
That's against company policy.

611
00:32:45,988 --> 00:32:47,473
Coffee and a bagel?

612
00:32:47,487 --> 00:32:49,451
Mmm... need a real reason.

613
00:32:49,468 --> 00:32:53,011
There was a $25,000 charge
made to the Casa Brazil

614
00:32:53,026 --> 00:32:55,271
- under "props and extras."
- And?

615
00:32:55,328 --> 00:32:57,583
Show me the props and extras.

616
00:32:57,596 --> 00:33:01,052
Models on a beach wearing bikinis--sand,
water, boobs.

617
00:33:01,068 --> 00:33:02,982
This could've been shot
for next to nothing.

618
00:33:02,997 --> 00:33:05,802
Okay, so maybe she was padding.
Everybody pads a little.

619
00:33:05,815 --> 00:33:08,581
A little? Daniel, $25,000?

620
00:33:08,596 --> 00:33:10,802
That's my family's
rent for a year.

621
00:33:10,818 --> 00:33:14,612
Betty, I can't question the creative
director of a major fashion magazine.

622
00:33:14,627 --> 00:33:17,621
Who's hiding a huge expense
under "props and extras."

623
00:33:17,635 --> 00:33:20,351
It's not right, and it's not
right when you do it, either.

624
00:33:20,365 --> 00:33:24,151
Point taken, but Oshi's due in two
hours. If we take Wilhelmina down--

625
00:33:24,166 --> 00:33:26,713
Then they cancel her company credit
card. She can't pay for Oshi,

626
00:33:26,746 --> 00:33:28,761
and your father will
never make her publisher.

627
00:33:28,778 --> 00:33:33,561
And I'm left with $327 to entertain
Oshi and his entire entourage.

628
00:33:33,627 --> 00:33:35,922
Then ditch the entourage.
Only take him to dinner,

629
00:33:35,936 --> 00:33:39,300
and don't tell me that
$327 isn't enough.

630
00:33:39,318 --> 00:33:40,660
Okay.

631
00:33:40,675 --> 00:33:44,372
All right, and how do we
prove Wilhelmina cheated? Hmm?

632
00:34:16,846 --> 00:34:19,183
Am I invited to
the dinner, Daniel?

633
00:34:19,198 --> 00:34:21,902
I don't think Masa
allows dishwashing

634
00:34:21,917 --> 00:34:23,703
as a form of payment.

635
00:34:23,968 --> 00:34:27,992
Actually, Wilhelmina, I was thinking
of something a bit more private.

636
00:34:28,008 --> 00:34:29,310
Were you?

637
00:34:29,325 --> 00:34:30,842
Oshi-san...

638
00:34:30,858 --> 00:34:34,900
in the spirit of minimalism,
and to honor your collection,

639
00:34:34,915 --> 00:34:37,860
uh, I was thinking we might
have our dinner one-on-one.

640
00:34:37,878 --> 00:34:41,850
You and me, alone,
so we can get to know each other.

641
00:34:43,968 --> 00:34:45,293
Alone?

642
00:34:46,426 --> 00:34:48,793
No. No, no.

643
00:34:48,806 --> 00:34:51,131
Oshi is...

644
00:34:51,715 --> 00:34:53,762
Oshi.

645
00:35:10,495 --> 00:35:12,503
I'm sorry.
There wasn't another way in.

646
00:35:12,515 --> 00:35:14,650
- Where's Henry?
- Meeting with your father.

647
00:35:14,665 --> 00:35:16,170
Is there any way
to hold them off?

648
00:35:16,188 --> 00:35:17,102
Why?

649
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:19,572
Because Oshi is Oshi,

650
00:35:19,586 --> 00:35:22,193
and we have $300
to feed 15 people.

651
00:35:22,208 --> 00:35:25,430
I mean, if we want him to stay at "Mode,"
we have to invite Wilhelmina along.

652
00:35:25,445 --> 00:35:28,933
No. No, no, then you lose, Daniel.
You can't just give up without a fight.

653
00:35:28,945 --> 00:35:32,000
Yeah, but we don't have a plan
"b," Betty. I don't have a choice.

654
00:35:34,808 --> 00:35:37,323
It's so minimal, it's nothing.

655
00:35:37,338 --> 00:35:39,290
Yes, yes.

656
00:35:39,307 --> 00:35:41,893
Simple is better.

657
00:35:42,085 --> 00:35:46,682
Round... white... minimal.

658
00:35:47,238 --> 00:35:49,670
Round, white...

659
00:35:49,685 --> 00:35:52,803
- Minimal. Kampai, Oshi.
- Kampai.

660
00:35:52,815 --> 00:35:55,442
Brilliant collection--brilliant
in its simplicity.

661
00:35:55,456 --> 00:35:58,823
- It's minimal, it's white--
- It's crazy. You can't be serious.

662
00:35:58,835 --> 00:36:01,291
It might work, Daniel,
and we have to try something.

663
00:36:01,308 --> 00:36:03,633
No, we don't, Betty. It's over.

664
00:36:03,645 --> 00:36:07,951
Party time, Daniel.
Oshi's ready for more champagne.

665
00:36:07,965 --> 00:36:11,101
Uh, well, we could drink more
champagne at Masa, Oshi.

666
00:36:11,116 --> 00:36:13,463
Isn't that right, Wilhelmina?

667
00:36:15,838 --> 00:36:18,013
I would love to come.

668
00:36:18,025 --> 00:36:20,601
I'm famished, Oshi, aren't you?

669
00:36:20,615 --> 00:36:24,242
Oshi's hungry, okay?
Very hungry.

670
00:36:26,175 --> 00:36:29,290
But he and your father will
know who paid the bill.

671
00:36:30,128 --> 00:36:32,290
Shall we move on to dinner?

672
00:36:32,306 --> 00:36:35,632
Actually, Wilhelmina,
I think you have more pressing business.

673
00:36:35,647 --> 00:36:37,790
May we see you for a moment?

674
00:36:38,627 --> 00:36:39,842
Bradford?

675
00:36:39,855 --> 00:36:43,603
It's about the last
issue's shoot in Rio.

676
00:36:44,095 --> 00:36:46,480
Uh... was there a problem?

677
00:36:46,498 --> 00:36:48,792
I don't mind paying
for props and extras,

678
00:36:48,805 --> 00:36:53,310
but I take great exception at
financing your brazilian butt lift.

679
00:36:57,697 --> 00:37:02,503
I'm sure you'll all have a
wonderful dinner without me.

680
00:37:12,418 --> 00:37:14,501
Stop looking at it.

681
00:37:15,895 --> 00:37:18,471
It may as well be Oshi
walking out the door.

682
00:37:18,485 --> 00:37:20,843
We have a plan "b," Daniel.

683
00:37:20,858 --> 00:37:22,661
You think so, Betty?

684
00:37:22,707 --> 00:37:24,412
I think we're screwed.

685
00:37:32,176 --> 00:37:33,682
This better work, Betty.

686
00:37:33,698 --> 00:37:37,260
He likes round, he likes white,
he likes minimal. It's perfect.

687
00:37:37,277 --> 00:37:38,371
Daniel?

688
00:37:38,848 --> 00:37:40,612
Taking him somewhere special?

689
00:37:40,627 --> 00:37:42,303
Someplace unique.

690
00:37:42,315 --> 00:37:44,282
Just remember you're
on your own dime.

691
00:37:44,298 --> 00:37:45,611
Kinda hard to forget, dad.

692
00:37:45,627 --> 00:37:46,881
Make sure you don't lose him.

693
00:37:46,896 --> 00:37:47,830
He won't.

694
00:37:50,048 --> 00:37:52,852
Good luck returning my ass!

695
00:37:58,308 --> 00:38:01,830
Oshi want to know
where we are going.

696
00:38:02,706 --> 00:38:05,671
- New Jersey.
- New Jersey?

697
00:38:16,217 --> 00:38:18,241
Holy crap.

698
00:38:18,366 --> 00:38:20,410
This is a disaster.

699
00:38:20,426 --> 00:38:22,050
I can feel it.

700
00:38:23,986 --> 00:38:25,501
Daniel!

701
00:38:25,766 --> 00:38:27,600
Yes, Oshi?

702
00:38:27,618 --> 00:38:29,821
What place is this?

703
00:38:29,835 --> 00:38:31,802
Where have you brought me?

704
00:38:32,415 --> 00:38:34,231
It's called...

705
00:38:34,897 --> 00:38:37,281
the White Tassel.

706
00:38:38,306 --> 00:38:43,750
It's clean, white, minimal.

707
00:38:44,527 --> 00:38:47,370
Round food inside.

708
00:38:51,246 --> 00:38:52,882
Minimal.

709
00:38:53,365 --> 00:38:54,911
He likes it.

710
00:38:54,927 --> 00:38:57,301
Oshi likes it.

711
00:39:04,445 --> 00:39:07,600
We've got exclusives for
his next four collections.

712
00:39:07,615 --> 00:39:09,660
"Minimal, Daniel."

713
00:39:09,676 --> 00:39:11,092
Yeah.

714
00:39:11,366 --> 00:39:15,022
Yeah. Thanks, dad.

715
00:39:15,358 --> 00:39:19,250
No, you have no idea how
much I appreciate that.

716
00:39:19,266 --> 00:39:21,651
Okay, yeah.

717
00:39:21,906 --> 00:39:24,272
He's reactivating my
company credit card.

718
00:39:24,288 --> 00:39:25,780
Yes!

719
00:39:25,796 --> 00:39:28,093
He's tough, but he's fair.

720
00:39:29,066 --> 00:39:31,021
And thanks for the lesson.

721
00:39:31,846 --> 00:39:34,581
It's not how much you have.
It's how you spend it.

722
00:39:34,595 --> 00:39:38,892
Yeah, I was thinking more like
the one about not giving up.

723
00:39:39,798 --> 00:39:41,873
Forget about it.

724
00:39:47,887 --> 00:39:49,093
Good night, Betty.

725
00:39:49,108 --> 00:39:50,583
Good night.

726
00:39:52,986 --> 00:39:54,492
Betty.

727
00:40:00,336 --> 00:40:03,253
I know. "Walter, go away."

728
00:40:04,456 --> 00:40:06,490
It's just a knockoff.

729
00:40:13,028 --> 00:40:14,692
It's wonderful.

730
00:40:35,508 --> 00:40:37,071
Nice bag.

731
00:40:38,865 --> 00:40:40,762
It truly is.

732
00:40:41,516 --> 00:40:44,340
Okay, forget the opera tickets.
Forget the taquitos.

733
00:40:44,358 --> 00:40:46,490
Final offer--body
